    "name": "Watch Duty",
    "description": "<p><strong>Watch Duty</strong> is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit providing free, real-time wildfire alerts to communities across the Western United States. Our service is powered by a network of trained, active and retired firefighters, dispatchers, and first responders who monitor fire activity around the clock.</p><p>Since launching, we've delivered over <strong>50 million alerts</strong> and helped countless families evacuate safely. Our reporting is trusted by fire departments, emergency managers, and everyday people who depend on accurate, timely information when it matters most.</p><h3>Our Mission</h3><p>We believe everyone deserves access to life-saving wildfire information — regardless of where they live or what they can afford. Watch Duty will always be free, ad-free, and community-supported.</p><h3>How We Work</h3><ul><li><strong>Real firefighters</strong> — not algorithms — monitor fire activity 24/7</li><li><strong>Hyper-local alerts</strong> pushed directly to your phone in seconds</li><li><strong>Live fire maps</strong> with perimeter data updated in real time</li><li><strong>Community reporting</strong> lets neighbors help neighbors stay informed</li></ul><p>Every dollar raised through our community goes directly toward keeping monitors staffed, servers running, and coverage expanding to new at-risk regions.</p>",
